Personal AI Agent (Browser-Based)

A lightweight browser-based personal AI assistant built using HTML, JavaScript, and the Anthropic Claude API.
This project allows users to interact with an AI agent directly from the browser by entering their own Anthropic API key, making it simple, secure, and fully client-side.

The agent maintains conversation history, responds intelligently using Claude models, and provides helpful suggestions through a built-in Next Steps recommendation system.

Project Overview

The Personal Agent is a minimal yet functional AI chat interface that demonstrates how to connect a frontend web application to a large language model API.

Instead of requiring a backend server, the project runs entirely in the browser and sends requests directly to the Anthropic API. This makes it easy to experiment with AI-powered assistants without complex setup.

Users can paste their API key, ask questions, and receive responses instantly while the system remembers previous messages to maintain conversation context.

Tech Stack

HTML5 – Structure of the application

JavaScript (Vanilla JS) – Logic and API interaction

Anthropic Claude API – AI language model responses

Fetch API – Sending HTTP requests to the AI service
